- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the challenges and solutions related to building and managing software workflows.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses scheduling algorithms for workflows.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is relevant as the paper discusses the computational requirements and resource provisioning for workflows.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still relevant as the paper discusses the automation of processes in workflows.
